In [5]:
class ReLU(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()

    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
        return torch.fmax(torch.zeros(x.size(), device=x.device), x)

In [7]:
class Linear(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, in_features, out_features):
        super().__init__()
        self.in_features = in_features
        self.out_features = out_features
        self.weight = torch.nn.Parameter(torch.empty((self.in_features, self.out_features)))
        self.bias = torch.nn.Parameter(torch.empty(out_features))
        self.reset_parameters()

    def reset_parameters(self):
        torch.nn.init.normal_(self.weight.data, 0.0, 0.01)
        torch.nn.init.zeros_(self.bias)

    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
        return x @ self.weight + self.bias

    def __repr__(self):
        return 'Linear({0:d}, {1:d})'.format(*self.weight.shape)

Реализация Softmax-слоя и функции потерь¶

$Softmax$ , : $$\hat y = \text{Softmax}(x) = \left \{\frac {\exp(x^i)}{\sum_{j=1}^K \exp(x^j)} \right \}_{i=1}^K, \quad K - \text{ .}$$

$x^i$ $i$- $x$.

(-: negative log likelihood NLL) $$L(y, \hat y) = -\sum_{i=1}^K \mathbb{1}[y = i]\log \hat y^i,$$ $\mathbb{1}[y = i]$ $i$- .

NLL - ( $y$, $\hat y$). , , $y$ : $$L(y, \hat y) = - \log \hat y_{y}$$

.

:

$$ \mathfrak{L} = \frac1N \sum_{i=1}^N L(y_i, \hat y_i) = \frac1N \sum_{i=1}^N L(y_i, \text{NN}_{\theta}(x_i)) \rightarrow \min_{\theta}\,,$$

$x_i$ $y_i$ $i$- , $\text{NN}_{\theta}$ , $x_i$ $\hat y_i$, $\theta$ , $N$ .

In [10]:
class CrossEntropyLoss(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()

    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor, labels: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
        d = x - torch.max(x, 1, keepdim = True)[0]
        res = d - (d).exp().sum(-1).log().unsqueeze(-1)
        return -res[range(labels.shape[0]), labels.long()].mean()

class DenseNetwork(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, in_features, hidden_size, n_classes, n_layers, activation=ReLU):
        super().__init__()

        self.in_features = in_features
        self.hidden_size = hidden_size
        self.n_classes = n_classes
        self.n_layers = n_layers
        self.activation = activation
        self.layers = torch.nn.Sequential()

        self.layers.append(Linear(in_features, hidden_size if n_layers > 1 else n_classes))
        if n_layers > 1:
            self.layers.append(self.activation())
            for _ in range(n_layers - 2):
                self.layers.append(Linear(hidden_size, hidden_size))
                self.layers.append(self.activation())
            self.layers.append(Linear(hidden_size, n_classes))

    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
        return self.layers(x)

training_loop:

In [26]:
import tqdm.notebook as tqdm

def training_loop(n_epochs, network, loss_fn, optimizer, ds_train, ds_test, device):
    train_losses, test_losses, train_accuracies, test_accuracies = [], [], [], []
    network = network.to(device)
    ds_train = (ds_train[0].to(device), ds_train[1].to(device))
    ds_test = (ds_test[0].to(device), ds_test[1].to(device))

    for epoch in tqdm.tqdm(range(n_epochs), total=n_epochs, leave=True):
        network.train()

        def closure():
            optimizer.zero_grad(set_to_none=True)
            cur = loss_fn(network(ds_train[0]) , ds_train[1])
            cur.backward()
            return cur

        optimizer.step(closure)
        network.eval()

        with torch.no_grad():
            lab_train = network(ds_train[0])
            corr_train = (lab_train.argmax(axis=1) == ds_train[1]).float().sum()
            cur = loss_fn(lab_train , ds_train[1])
            train_losses.append(cur)
            train_accuracies.append(corr_train * 100 / len(ds_train[1]))

            lab_test = network(ds_test[0])
            corr_test = (lab_test.argmax(axis=1) == ds_test[1]).float().sum()
            cur = loss_fn(lab_test, ds_test[1])
            test_losses.append(cur)
            test_accuracies.append(corr_test * 100 / len(ds_test[1]))

            if epoch % 20 == 0:
                print(
                    'Loss (Train/Test): {0:.3f}/{1:.3f}. Accuracy, % (Train/Test): {2:.2f}/{3:.2f}'.format(
                        train_losses[-1], test_losses[-1], train_accuracies[-1], test_accuracies[-1]
                    )
                )

    return train_losses, test_losses, train_accuracies, test_accuracies

In [76]:
def initialize_module(module, init):
    if isinstance(module, torch.nn.Linear):  # ,     
        if init == 'Kaiming':
            torch.nn.init.kaiming_uniform_(module.weight, nonlinearity='relu')
        elif init == 'Xavier':
            torch.nn.init.xavier_uniform_(module.weight)
        elif isinstance(init, float):
            torch.nn.init.normal_(module.weight, mean=0, std=init)

def my_w(n):
    for i, v in enumerate(init_vars):
        for j in range(accs_train.shape[0]):
            dn = DenseNetwork(in_features, hidden_size, n_classes, n, ReLU)
            initialize_module(dn, init_vars[i])
            dn.to(device)
            train_losses, test_losses, train_accs, test_accs = training_loop(200, dn, CrossEntropyLoss(), torch.optim.LBFGS(dn.parameters(), max_iter=1), (X_train, y_train), (X_test, y_test), device)
            accs_train[i, j] = train_accs[-1].cpu().item()
            accs_test[i, j] = test_accs[-1].cpu().item()
    return accs_train, accs_test

        accs_train_on_iterations.append(train_accs)

$2$ : Tanh Sigmoid.

In [142]:
class Tanh(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.activation = torch.tanh

    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
        return self.activation(x)

    def __repr__(self):
        return 'Tanh()'
In [143]:
class Sigmoid(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.activation = torch.special.expit

    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
        return self.activation(x)

    def __repr__(self):
        return 'Sigmoid()'

        initialize_module(dn, init_vars[i])
        res = training_loop(200, dn, CrossEntropyLoss(), torch.optim.LBFGS(dn.parameters(), max_iter = 1), (X_train, y_train), (X_test, y_test), device)
        accs_train[i, j] = res[2][len(res[2])-1]
        accs_test[i, j] = res[3][len(res[3])-1]
